ref: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.111, p.265 (1968)
title: Elastic scattering of 52 MeV deuterons

x4freetext: Elastic scattering of 52 MeV deuterons

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.111, p.265 (1968)

x4freetext: Telescopes consisting of 200 mu-m-
-400 mu-m Si surface-barrier counters as dE-counters
and NaI(Tl) scintillation counters as E-counters. A
few differential cross sections are taken with a Ge(Li)
detector as E-counter. In the case of 3,4He targets,
the differential cross sections at backward angles
have been obtained by measuring the recoil nuclei
scattered in forward angles with a telescope containing
a 2 mm Si surface-barrier detector as E-counter. In
the case of lH(d,d)lH, the differential cross sections
at backward angles are measured by the detection of the
protons with Ge(Li) detector as E-counter in the
telescope.
Digitizing error
Digitizing error
The statistical error

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: The total error in the absolute cross
section results from the following components:
(i) current and charge measurement,
(ii) aperture geometry,
(iii) detector and
(iv) target thickness determination.
The over-all energy resolution is about 600 keV with
the NaI(Tl) detectors and about 250 keV with Ge(Li)
and Si detectors as E-counters.

x4freetext: The measurements on 1H were performed using a gas
target with a diameter of 10 cm and a volume of
about 1 l, which is inserted into the scattering
chamber instead of target. In the reaction plane, the
particles pass through a slit which is covered by a
4.6 mg/cm2 thick havar foil.
The maximum pressure is 500 mm Hg.
